ISTE NIT Durgapur witnessed a glorious ,splendid and memorable session and extends its heartfelt gratitude and privilege to all the office bearers who worked hard relentlessly for the society taking it to the zenith of glory. We extend them our best wishes hoping that they would succeed in all  their future endeavours.  With the onset of a new session ,its time to pass on the responsibilites to the juniors hoping that they would also follow the footprints of their seniors  further  enriching the society , enhancing its grandeur and reaching new heights under their leadership. ISTE NIT  Durgapur heartily welcomes the new office bearers .Best wishes and Congratulations to all of them!! 1) Chairperson :- Harshit Anand 
2) Vice-Chairperson :- Ankan Ghosh 
3) General Secretary :- M. Aruna 
4) Treasurer :- Priyam Sinha 
5) Assistant General Secretary :- Rohan Biswas 
6) Public Relations Head :- Prashanna Sharma 
7) Logistics Head :- (I) Deepa Kumari (II) Sumit Singh 
8) Graphics Design Head :- Priyam Sinha 
9) Web Development Head :- Ankan Ghosh 
10) Sponsorship Head :- Harshit Anand 
11) Other Executive Committee :- Members (I) Shivam Rajput (II) Abhinav Prakash (III) Shrutika Nigam (IV) Amit Dalai

Showcase your inner businessman, and let your innovative product idea come to life! Here’s your opportunity to UP THE ANTE!

Participants are free to choose their own products- it may be real or fictional, and it can undertone a serious or funny direction. For example, a brochure presenting technology for voice activation in lifts; or a flyer selling phone holders to watch movies while lying in bed. Bonus points will be given for inventive ideas, and for presenting as an advertisement. 
The best ideas aren’t made by playing safe; so we encourage you to step out of your box and go wild with creativity!

NOTE- Submissions can be sent on the Google form link found in the bio.

#ideas #entrepreneurship #innovate #spectrum #iste #staytuned

Get those artistic knobs turning in RETROSPECTIVE! Drawing inspiration from enigmatic scientists around the world, create a poster or digital art that does justice to their contributions. The submission must revolve solely around the lives, works or achievements of the scientist. 
NOTE- Submissions can be sent on the Google form link found in the bio.

#digitalart #retrospective #spectrum #iste #staytuned

Get your pencils, brushes, and paints ready as we present to you TANDEM ART! Here's the twist- only two colours can be used to create your masterpiece. 
Think you are up for the challenge? Any medium- watercolour, acrylic, colour pencils, sketch pens etc- are allowed (except pencil shading or charcoal based mediums). Blend your art skills with your perspective about mental health, and let’s make the world a better place. 
NOTE- Submissions can be sent on the Google form link found in the bio.

Calling out all science enthusiasts! CRYSTAL CLEAR challenges you to test your brains and your dexterity with this fun event. Portray the Newton within you to gain some hands-on skills while staying indoors.

Rules for the laws:
1.	Pascal’s law- For this, you need to demonstrate one application of the law.
2.	Archimedes’ law- For this, you need to measure the weight of a substance.
3.	Law of conservation of momentum- For this, you need to measure the velocities and prove this law.

NOTE- Submissions can be sent on the Google form link found in the bio

With the motto of ‘a picture speaks a thousand words’, we present PIXELS. It has been rightly said that home is where the heart is. We invite all those individuals who live behind their lens to capture their hometown at its best and send in their creative entries. 
NOTE- Submissions can be sent on the Google form link found in the bio.

Have a keen eye for any mysterious activities around you? SLEUTH'S VISION gives you the opportunity to voice your craziest conspiracy theories! 
The participants have to pen down an original short story, poem OR a sonnet, which must be a mixture of their imagination with some true facts. For example, the short story they write may address the global economic situation and its repercussions; or a poem themed on social media propaganda. 
After all, the pen is mightier than the sword. 
NOTE- Submissions can be sent on the Google form link found in the bio.

For all those coding connoisseurs and the quarantine dabblers, SPECTRUM presents to you its mystery event- DREAM CODEX. With a one-of-a-kind collaboration under way, experience a unique coding challenge as you test your skills against competitors from around the country. Don’t miss this opportunity to go head to head with other enthusiasts. 
We wish all candidates the best of luck as you embark on a week-long coding extravaganza.

“Dad: A son’s first hero, a daughter’s first love.” When it comes to the one man in your life whom  you can always look up to, is your father. A real Ironman who stands by his children in all situations. He is the one who teaches us the right values of life and picks us up whenever  we fail, gives us the strength and courage to fight back again.  No matter whatever problems he is facing in his life, he will do his best not to show them to you so that you can stay happy. It's our moral responsibility as a son , as a daughter to look after him in all possible ways especially when he  is old and dependented . Acknowledging  this precious and unconditional bond, every year Father’s Day is celebrated on 21st June this year.
 On  this auspicious day ,ISTE NIT Durgapur Student’s Chapter salutes all fathers  and wishes a “Happy father’s day" advising all to spare your time for your parents. Go to them, have a chat with them, touch them with love. Share some old memories, and make their  journey as much happy as you can !!

The clock is ticking! Gear up for a week of fun activities for Spectrum is just one day away! Immerse yourself in a plethora of events to compete against people from all over the country. 
And that’s not all, the winner’s works will be featured on each ISTE’s Instagram and Facebook pages! So grab this opportunity to showcase your talents, and break free from your humdrum routine.

Note, Plagiarism in any form will not be tolerated. If found, the corresponding entry will be nullified immediately.

#spectrum 
#onedaytogo

#iste #staytuned

International Yoga Day
OM SHANTI
Yoga - Unison of mind, body, and soul, with the highest spiritual aura. The propitious ceremony of the International Yoga Day is commemorated on the 21st June, on the Summer Solstice, since 2015, after the proclamation, by our most reverenced, Prime Minister, Shri Narendra Modi. The day aims to advance the divine glory of Yoga which has infinite benedictions upon our health. Besides, it leads us to our spiritual realms. The providential occasion promotes to acknowledge and advocate Yoga in our everyday life's so that it could get its tranquility and divine fulfillment. After getting the obeisance from the UN, the whole world is striving to aggrandize themselves to the seraphic godsends of Yoga. But due to the COVID 19 pandemic, the UN preconized the theme of "Yoga for Health-Yoga at Home", to incentivize us to face the iniquity, existing in the whole world.
 Therefore, being filled with celestial sparkle, ISTE NIT Durgapur Student's Chapter proselytize the deific spirit of the International Yoga Day.
#yoga #yogapractice #yogainspiration #yogaeverydamnday #yogaposes #yogalife #yogaeveryday #yogateacher  #yogalove #yogaeverywhere #yogafun #yogaaddict #covid19 #corona #yogaday2020 #yogachallenge #yogacommunity #healthylifestyle #health

Unveiling, the list of events for Spectrum! 
RULES:
1. The event will be live everyday at 8 am.
2. The participant has to submit their entries via the Google form link which will be available on our bio.
3. The deadline for the submission of entries for each event is 11:59 pm of the following day.
4. Submissions will not be accepted after the deadline.
5. Plagiarised content will be immediately disqualified.
6. E-certificates will be given to all participants.

Tune in everyday from 22nd to 28th June to take up the daily challenge.

#iste #spectrum #staytuned
